benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/invoiceItems/{invoiceItemId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve invoice item audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: Scenario TC01 covers successful retrieval with valid invoice item ID.
Empty Response: Scenario TC02 covers case when no audit logs are present for an existing invoice item.
Invalid invoice item ID format: Scenario TC04 tests malformed UUID input.
Non-existent invoice item: Scenario TC03 covers not found case with 404 response.
Authorization: Scenarios TC05 and TC06 cover missing and invalid tokens respectively.
Extra query parameters: Scenario TC07 tests ignoring unsupported parameters.
System/database unavailable: Scenario TC08 covers 503 error during downtime.
Large audit log history: Scenario TC09 tests handling large payloads and performance.
SQL injection: Scenario TC10 tests injection prevention.
XSS attempt: Scenario TC11 tests reflected XSS protection.
Regression: Scenario TC12 ensures previously fixed fields are present.
Backward compatibility: Scenario TC13 covers older client headers.
Concurrent requests: Scenario TC14 tests multiple simultaneous calls.
Response time: Scenario TC15 addresses performance under load.
Content-Type header: Scenario TC16 verifies correct header.
Partial input: Scenario TC17 tests incomplete UUID handling.
Empty database: Scenario TC18 covers no invoice items in system.
gaps: Pagination: No tests cover handling of large datasets with pagination.
Caching Behavior: No scenarios test for ETag, Cache-Control headers, or caching strategies.
Rate Limiting: No tests simulate multiple rapid requests to verify throttling or rate limits.
Edge cases for malformed or special characters beyond injection/XSS are not explicitly tested.
Response body validation: No detailed checks on the structure or completeness of AuditLog objects beyond presence of fields.
recommendations: Add tests for pagination to verify correct handling of large result sets.
Include scenarios that verify caching headers and cache invalidation strategies.
Implement rate limiting tests to ensure system handles high request volumes gracefully.
Expand validation of response bodies to ensure all fields are correctly returned and formatted.
Test additional edge cases such as special characters, very long IDs, or boundary UUID values.
